    oakcurric:thread-developing-grammatical-knowledge .

oakcurric:unit-3773
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "'The Three Little Pigs': reading and writing"@en ;
  curric:slug "the-three-little-pigs-reading-and-writing" ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit, pupils read and respond to the traditional tale 'The Three Little
  Pigs'. Pupils first read the story, and look at it from different perspectives, before
  then writing their own version of the story."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit uses and builds on pupils' understanding of traditional tales
  from 'The Magic Porridge Pot'. In this unit, pupils are introduced to another traditional
  tale, and explore different ways of building and structuring a simple story. This unit
  prepares pupils for their next traditional tale unit, 'Jack and the Beanstalk', where they
  will practise reading and writing another traditional tale.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3773-1 ,
