oakcurric:unit-3770
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Following and writing instructions to make a sandwich: reading and writing"@en ;
  curric:slug "following-and-writing-instructions-to-make-a-sandwich-reading-and-writing" ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit, pupils practise following and writing instructions. They first
  design a sandwich and look at the features of instructions, before writing their set of
  instructions."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit uses and builds on pupils' understanding of writing from 'The
  Magic Porridge Pot'. This unit builds on that initial understanding as pupils start to write
  basic instructions, and think about writing for a very specific and useful purpose. This unit
  prepares pupils for the unit 'Looking after pets', where pupils will develop their ability to
  write commands.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3770-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3770-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3770-3 ,
