  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-english-key-stage-1 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-fiction-reading-spine .

oakcurric:unit-977
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "'The Wolf, The Duck and the Mouse': book club"@en ;
  curric:slug "the-wolf-the-duck-and-the-mouse-book-club" ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit, pupils read and explore the narrative text, 'The Wolf, The Duck and
  the Mouse'. They explore the characters, setting and plot and summarise and retell the
  story. Finally, they identify and discuss the key themes in the text."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit uses and builds on pupils' understanding of narrative, which was
  explored in the prior unit 'Yoshi the Stonecutter'. Pupils will broaden their reading
  experiences to a richer, higher quality text. They will explore some of the precise and
  ambitious vocabulary used in the text and build their understanding through summarising the
  story verbally. This unit prepares pupils to analyse a character in more depth, which will be
  explored in the future unit, 'The Planet in a Pickle Jar', a narrative written from a
  character's perspective.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-977-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-977-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-977-3 ,
